{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reset the Windrush Compensation Scheme with free legal assistance for victims",
        "additional_details": "The Windrush scandal remains a profound state failure. Yet, victims are denied the same justice as Post Office and Infected Blood scandal victims.\r\n \r\nTheir compensation scheme is run by the Home Office \u2013 the department that caused the scandal. It is slow, complex, and denies victims legal assistance, resulting in low offers and delayed justice.\r\n \r\nIt is time to end this two-tier system of justice. The Windrush generation built Britain; they deserve the same dignity and esteem.",
        "background": "We call on the Government to:\r\n1. Move the Windrush Compensation Scheme out of the Home Office to a fully independent body.\r\n2. Provide guaranteed, non-means-tested legal assistance for all claimants.\r\n3. Expand the scheme to include all losses, like military pensions.",
